do you save money for emergences kids education retirement what else how do you manage to save for all this if you are a single mom i learned that if ever i don't have enough to save at least a little bit each month i'm probably spending too much for a while i had to cut out a bunch of non essentials to boost my savings cable tv cell phones or a home phone internet new clothes shoes dinners movies out all these are non essentials in fact i realized i was paying way too much for my apartment and got a smaller one if you go just one month without those unessential things you're likely to save a few hundred bucks can you make it months you just saved at least a thousand if you cut your expenses to the bare bones and still can't save anything look at your income can you get a part time job can you babysit or mow lawns or deliver pizzas cash in cash out savings bring more in or send less out or both that's the only way to save Personal finance Warren Buffett Friends Lawn mower Son Goku (Dragon Ball) Broadband Internet access GSM services Major League Baseball television contracts Sin City Ron and Fez Day care The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Flat tax About a Boy Unconditional Love Humphrey Bogart Insurance Videotex Married... with Children Make money fast Treehouse of Horror IV Avenue Q Freeters W. Daniel Hillis The Inside Gross domestic product Surveillance Sears Holdings Corporation Charles Ponzi Great Teacher Onizuka $ale of the Century Hyperinflation Phoebe Halliwell Capitalism Live 8 Inflation The Apprentice 3 Ocean's Twelve FairTax Lawn Life insurance Satchel Paige Dot-com Empire Burlesque Vegeta The Adventures of Pete & Pete Futurama (TV series - season 1) Everwood Arthur Laffer Futurama (TV series - season 2) Rent (musical) Le p__re Goriot Series finale Poker jargon Kill Bill The Brady Bunch CPU design Hurricane preparedness for New Orleans Year 2000 problem The Amazing Race Schindler's List American Red Cross Social Security debate (United States) Internet fraud 